ning of the gospel of Jesus Christ, the Son of God;"},{"id":"recOngjVfCUywgHAO","ref":"Mark.1.2","text":"As it is written in the prophets, Behold, I send my messenger before thy face, which shall prepare thy way before thee."},{"id":"recB9woRJA7ai8U0J","ref":"Mark.1.3","text":"The voice of one crying in the wilderness, Prepare ye the way of the Lord, make his paths straight."},{"id":"rectgI6Cq4qLDyaWF","ref":"Mark.1.4","text":"John did baptize in the wilderness, and preach the baptism of repentance for the remission of sins."},{"id":"recQL7bFWIJON2g5h","ref":"Mark.1.5","text":"And there went out unto him all the land of Judaea, and they of Jerusalem, and were all baptized of him in the river of Jordan, confessing their sins."},{"id":"recrfQlWqFAUFxnRR","ref":"Mark.1.6","text":"And John was clothed with camel’s hair, and with a girdle of a skin about his loins; and he did eat locusts and wild honey;"},{"id":"recnWSEXc9Tt94Yb4","ref":"Mark.1.7","text":"And preached, saying, There cometh one mightier than I after me, the latchet of whose shoes I am not worthy to stoop down and unloose."},{"id":"recA6faesliy4YgEq","ref":"Mark.1.8","text":"I indeed have baptized you with water: but he shall baptize you with the Holy Ghost."}]}
